name: invalid_utf8_lone_low_surrogate
description: |
  This is the three-byte sequence ED B0 80, the direct UTF-8 encoding that a
  permissive encoder might emit for the lone low surrogate U+DC00. Surrogate
  code points are not Unicode scalar values and are excluded from well-formed
  UTF-8, so a conforming encoder must fail rather than produce these bytes.

  The low-surrogate case complements U+D800: rejecting only high surrogates
  leaves a range-checking bug in encoders and decoders.

  See the Unicode definition of well-formed UTF-8 (D92 and Table 3-7):
  https://www.unicode.org/versions/Unicode15.0.0/ch03.pdf
format: hex
decode-as: bytes
invalid-as: utf8
tags:
  - "encoding"
  - "unicode"
  - "utf8"
  - "invalid-utf8"
  - "surrogate"
  - "lone-surrogate"
  - "low-surrogate"
---
ed b0 80   # Invalid direct UTF-8 encoding of U+DC00
